        "instruction": "Apply the distributive property.",
        "work": "3x − 6 = 2x + 2",
        "explanation": "3(x − 2) = 3x − 6 and 2(x + 1) = 2x + 2."
      },
      {
        "subgoalLabel": "Collect variable terms",
        "instruction": "Subtract 2x from both sides.",
        "work": "x − 6 = 2",
        "explanation": "3x − 2x = x on the left."
      },
      {
        "subgoalLabel": "Isolate x",
        "instruction": "Add 6 to both sides.",
        "work": "x = 8",
        "explanation": "The solution is x = 8."
      },
      {
        "subgoalLabel": "Verify",
        "instruction": "Check in the original equation.",
        "work": "Left: 3(8 − 2) = 3(6) = 18. Right: 2(8 + 1) = 2(9) = 18. ✓",
        "explanation": "Both sides equal 18."
      }
    ]
  }
